issues.body:
Currently, the non-normative example of a decoded request object in the spec has a string type `urn:dio:action_id` claim in `id_token` section:
```
{
  ...
  "claims": {
    "id_token": {
      "urn:dio:action_id": "496a3ba7-04b4-4362-b775-9e0433e48eea",
      "acr": {
        "essential": true,
        "values": ["urn:cds.au:cdr:3"]
      }
    },
    ...
  },
  ...
}
```

However, according to https://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html#IndividualClaimsRequests, `id_token` members must be either `null` or a JSON object.
